-- Citigroup appoints new head of British operations
-- By Clare Hutchison
-- Mon Feb 03, 2014 07:21AM EST
-- None



LONDON, Feb 3 (Reuters) - Citigroup <C.N> has appointed one of its leading corporate bankers as head of its British operations, where he will be manage the bank's relationships with UK regulators and government, it said in a memo on Monday.

Former engineer James Bardrick joined Citi in 1987 and took charge of corporate and investment banking for Europe, Middle East and Africa alongside Manuel Falco four years ago. Bardrick replaces Maurice Thompson, the former SG Warburg global head of equity capital markets who had run Citi's UK franchise since 2012. Thompson has resigned to pursue interests outside the banking industry, the memo said.